This aircraft is capable of long range cruising in the early days of the war.<br/>Despite being unarmored and slow, it had a great operational range, and at the early days of hostilities was the main attack aircraft of the Carrier Task Force.<br/>Called the "Type 97 Attack Aircraft", it was mainly used for torpedo bombing of enemy ships, but was gradually phased out of that role.

